12 Section 3. Section 80-6-1105, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "80-6-1105. Alfalfa leaf-cutting bees -- certification. (1) A person possessing or controlling alfalfa
14 leaf-cutting bees in the state of Montana may annually certify all or part of the person's bees as provided in this
15 section.
16 (2) To certify bees, a person shall file a completed application form provided by the department,
17 together with a fee set by rule. The applicant shall provide the following:
18 (a) name and place of residence;
19 (b) the general location and number of bees to be certified; and
20 (c) other relevant information as may be required by committee department rule.
21 (3) After receipt of an application for certification, a sample of the total population of bees to be
22 certified must be selected by the committee department or its agent in a manner prescribed by the committee
23 department. The sample must be analyzed for pathogens, parasites, predators, nest destroyers, and live larvae
24 count. If certification standards are met, the sample must be certified.
25 (4) All bees to be certified may be stored in containers that can be officially sealed after sampling
26 to maintain their certification identity.
27 (5) When the committee department has in its possession a completed application form, an
28 appropriate fee, and a report that the sample meets certification standards, it may issue a certificate for the
